@node Fi "Rainboot3 Guide    Copyright 1996-2000 by Andreas Falkenhahn & Kimmo Pekkola"

    Hi!

    Welcome to a new, major update of Rainboot3. This version
    mostly features bug fixes and many many code optimizations
    and of course also improvements. Have a look at the history
    to see what has exactly changed. 
 
    The WINDOW emulation mode is now much more stable and supports
    also remapping of brushes and background pictures. Remapping
    of animbrushes is still to come (but it's near!). Maybe I'll
    also try to support fades in WINDOW mode, but this would be
    very hard to program.

    Finally I'm happy to announce you, that Rainboot v3.0 will be
    an all-in-one Rainboot including the features of Rainboot Pro
    (yeah!). I'm working on it and the release isn't too far away.
    But first I'm going to release RB2Exe, which converts a Rainboot
    configuration into a fully, stand-alone Amiga executable. Rainboot
    v2.9 is already prepared for this, although you won't notice it. 
   
    As I reprogrammed quite many things in this release, you'll
    probably notice some bugs. If you do so, please report them to
    me immediately. Thank you!
 
    Now have fun with Rainboot v2.9 - still the ultimate Multimedia
    boot experience!

    Kind regards,

                   Andreas

    Andreas Falkenhahn (aka Software Failure of Airsoft Softwair)
    Coder, Powered up with Amiga 1200T, Blizzard T-ERC 68040,
    http://airsoft.home.pages.de, ICQ: 42908277, IRC: SFA
   
@endnode

@node Fh "Rainboot3 Guide    Copyright 1996-2000 by Andreas Falkenhahn & Kimmo Pekkola"
    
